  "texts": [
    "Implants These are small, rod-shaped devices that are inserted under the skin of the arm and release hormones over time to prevent pregnancy.",
    "They are over 99% effective and can last for up to 3-5 years.Intrauterine Devices (IUDs) These devices are inserted into the uterus and release hormones or have a copper coating that prevents pregnancy.",
    "They are over 99% effective and can last for up to 5-10 years, depending on the type.",
    "Vasectomy This is a surgical procedure for men that involves cutting and sealing the vas deferens, the tubes that carry sperm from the testicles to the penis.",
    "It is over 99% effective and is a permanent form of birth control."
  ],
